attributes.documentation:
CDO is a generic, unopinionated implementation of a Collateralized
Debt Obligation credit derivative built on the Dharma Protocol.
It contains the core business logic for creating and
executing a trustless CDO. This includes any number of
tranche classes, shares per class, and different
interest rates and risk scores per tranche.

 * NOTE:
Tranche levels are represented in descending priority
order starting from 0. Ex. trancheLevel 0 = SENIOR Tranche.

 * All for loops in this contract are used to create a generic
implementation and are safe from block gas limits because
they run for the number of tranches which in a real-life
situation won't be excessive.

 * TODO:
GAS OPTIMIZATION:
Gas optimize through ordering of variable declarations
and sizes. Code has been left in a readable / organized manner.

 * Also most methods will be moved to CDOLib once a new design
of: CDOFactory -> Proxy -> CDOLib is complete. This allows for
code re-use and upgradeability.

 * TRUSTLESS UPGRADABILITY:
Currently the CDO owner can switch external contracts used at will.

 * Author: Devan Purhar
attributes.name: CDO
